These are the list of current releases,oldstable releases,historic releases,and future releases
The releases codename are actually used from geometry dash players and geometry dash spin-off/expansion example meltdown which is geometry dash spin-off/expansion and Viprin Is a geometry dash player
The releases might be actuallt X.0-X.999 Then After X.999 Then To X.0 Example 1.0-1.999 After 1.999 Then 2.0-2.999 After 2.999 3.0 And More 
The Testing or unstable or Development Branch Of Syslack would be anaban since Anaban is a notorious and infamous hacker in the Geometry Dash community who was active around 2016–2018 Example Syslack Linux (Post-stable development Anaban) For the next release
The Future Releases Are in Anaban Branch so these future releases will be released when Haikal decides they are ready.
None means there is no codename
EOL date for both current oldstable release and oldstable release will be added after the next release is released and become current stable release

